Package common.model

Contains Entity objects central to SixesWIlD

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ICopy
    Interface to show copyable behavior.
    ISource
    Interface that describes behavior for fill from sources.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractContainer
    Defines a subclass of AbstractSquares which can contain Tile Objects.
    AbstractLevel
    Defines a framework for all Level objects, which can be built and played.
    AbstractMove
    Defines Move objects/classes.
    AbstractSquare
    AbstractSquare defines any object which can be placed on a board.
    AbstractType
    Allows Classes to be represented by a user defined String.
    Board
    Board that contains all abstract squares for the game and is copyable.
    BoardTester  
    EmptySquare
    Empty square in the board.
    FreqTester  
    Frequency
    Frequency object that contains a value, frequency, and priority.
    FrequencyList
    Stores and manages a number of frequency objects.
    LevelList
    HashTable that holds all levels in the game.
    LevelListTester  
    LevelParameters
    Holds all the level parameters in a level(moves, thresholds, frequencies, board, and tile fillfrom sources).
    RandomSource
    Random source for a specific tile to fill from.
    ReferenceMap
    Stores information about where Squares in certain board positions should fill from in relation to other board positions.
    ScoreThresholds
    Contains the score thresholds to get 1,2,and 3 stars in a game.
    Selection
    This class is used by Controllers when making selections on the board.
    SerializationUtil
    A simple class with generic serialize and deserialize method implementations.
    Square
    Square contains whether it is selected is a regular square that can hold tiles.
    TestCopy  
    TestLevelParameters  
    TestMove  
    TestRefMap  
    TestSelection  
    TestThresholds  
    TestTile  
    Tile
    Tile contains a value and a bonus value.
